- Memory cells are ordered pairs (address, value)
- Prove permutation: written cells sorted by address
- Consecutive addresses with same address вҶ’ only one value possible
```

**Field Element Operations:**

```cairo
// All operations mod p
let a: felt = 10;
let b: felt = 20;
let c: felt = a + b;  // = 30 (mod p)

// Wrapping
let max: felt = p - 1;
let overflow: felt = max + 5;  // = 4 (mod p)

// No native comparison
// Must use asserts and range checks
```

